quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  2,38,"We said, "Go down from here, all of you. Then, should some guidance come to you from Me, those who follow My guidance shall have no fear, nor shall they grieve."
  2,39,"As for those who disbelieve, and deny Our signs, they are the people of the Fire - they shall be there forever.""
  2,40,"0 Children of Isra'il (the Israelites), remember My blessing that I conferred upon you, and fulfil the covenant with Me, so I fulfill your covenant, and have awe of Me alone."
  2,41,"And have faith in what I have revealed, confirming what is already with you, and do not be the first to deny it, nor take a paltry price for My signs. And fear Me alone."
  2,42,"And do not confound truth with falsehood, and do not hide the truth when you know."
  2,43,"And be steadfast in Salah, and pay Zakah, and bow down with those who bow."
  2,44,"Do you bid others to righteousness while you ignore your ownselves, although you keep reciting the Book? Have you then no sense?"
  2,45,"And seek help through patience and prayer. And it is indeed exacting, but not for the humble in heart"
  2,46,"who bear in mind that they are to meet their Lord, and that to Him they are to return."
  2,47,"0 Children of Isra'il (the Israelites), remember My blessing that I conferred upon you, and that I gave you excellence over the worlds."
  2,48,"And guard yourselves against a day when no one shall stand for anyone for anything, nor shall intercession be accepted on one's behalf, nor shall ransom be taken from one and neither shall they be given support."